cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the problem of anomaly detection in X-ray security imagery using convolutional neural networks. The paper focuses on segmentation strategies to enable object level and sub-component level anomaly detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with security screening, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of automated screening approaches and anomaly detection involves the use of machine learning, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach over an extensive dataset, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
